caption_original:
On Monday, 87 Plains Bison calves were moved from Elk Island National Park to the Blackfeet Nation Reservation in Montana, their ancestral homeland. Partnering with Iinnii Initiative has been a unique conservation initiative and an international success. 
Happy homecoming bison!
 Wildlife Conservation Society WCS Canada Oakland Zoo
caption_cleaned: On Monday, Plains Bison calves were moved from Elk Island National Park to the Blackfeet Nation Reservation in Montana, their ancestral homeland. Partnering with Iinnii Initiative has been a unique conservation initiative and an international success. Happy homecoming bison! Wildlife Conservation Society WCS Canada Oakland Zoo

caption_original:
Did you know that the Greater Sage-Grouse is Canada’s rarest endangered bird? This year, there are approximately 60 of them left in the country. 
That is why Grasslands National Park, in partnership with the University of Alberta, is undertaking a habitat restoration project. #WildlifeWeek
caption_cleaned: Did you know that the Greater Sage-Grouse is Canada’s rarest endangered bird? This year, there are approximately of them left in the country. That is why Grasslands National Park, in partnership with the University of Alberta, is undertaking a habitat restoration project.

Meet Poca and Terra! 
The Bar U Ranch National Historic Site new Percheron horses have been named!

caption_original:
Artist / filmmaker / explorer Cory Trepanier's fourth painting expedition of his "Into The Arctic" project begins with two weeks canoeing the Thomsen River in Aulavik National Park on the north end of Banks Island. 
In part 1, Cory and his crew land at the park’s green cabin and set off by canoe. During these first few days downriver, they encounter muskox, peregrine falcons and explore the vast arctic tundra. 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R2Eg-_XwRfk
